{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "615454d7b5df1240fa029b44", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fec2b295b085ab6eb92"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "31", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "A body is orbiting very close to the earth's surface with kinetic energy <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>. The energy required to completely escape from it is", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "7Fveu", "text": "<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "4yWu1", "text": "<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">2K</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "753h2", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "CidB4", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">3K</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "For a satellite in a closed orbit, we know that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>.</mo></math><br /><br />Hence, in order to make the body escape, we should make its total energy&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math>, which can be achieved by providing additional energy equal to the kinetic energy of the body itself as from the abiove relation we can clearly see that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mo>.</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>.</mo></math>.<br /><br />So, the energy given to the body so as to completely escape from its orbit is equal to its kinetic energy <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math>.", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61964c7d0464ec48eebad3e0", "61e7bd7e6b5fb113f0acb24c", "616023d0c98042c9b38a7982", "61c089b2a61e4eb3e272a598", "61964c7cb670fcf043c4b446", "616023d2145ccffd4235bb42", "616023cfe4a89d96c568e4cf", "61bb8228aa33ae8ae3f09705", "616023d351fc6e088c80fe27", "616023d1aaba018d1712f011", "62962122c5888d21e89ca99b", "629109ec59cb8652edec1bbc", "629f3a90bd521fefb89eaea5", "629f390baae215e1113a73a0", "64eb06c13118f713ecfef082", "66d58553a75f05ee8564f662", "67921d631d5b5072da5e9aa3", "67fdff47378e1624ea7b698e", "6809202b3a10446a207fdee0"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de4